00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:39.530
and when it was securelyfastened it was said to becinched.

285
00:29:39.530 --> 00:29:43.700
I don't know who said it, and itcould have been me,

286
00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:50.270
that a civilization is foundedin a crop and survives by a codeof law.

287
00:29:50.270 --> 00:29:53.300
Well the Spaniards introducedmany of the basic Americancrops;

288
00:29:53.300 --> 00:30:00.630
oats, wheat. barley, orangesand they took the rudestindigenous cereal of the Indian

289
00:30:00.630 --> 00:30:04.730
and they made it a staple fromthe Canadian border to the tipof South America -

290
00:30:04.730 --> 00:30:09.730
that's maize, what is everywherecalled corn.

291
00:30:20.470 --> 00:30:24.970
Two thousand miles to the northand east though a very differentway of life

292
00:30:24.970 --> 00:30:29.170
was being developed by the toughdescendants of those Bretonfishermen.

293
00:30:29.170 --> 00:30:33.700
They were exploring the watersand tracking down the game ofthat yawning stretch of forest

294
00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:36.700
and tundra in - Le Canada.

295
00:30:47.030 --> 00:30:51.500
Furs, especially beaver, were infashionable demand in Europe,

296
00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:55.600
and to get them the Frenchdeveloped an entirely new breedof explorers,

297
00:30:55.600 --> 00:30:56.970
trappers and hunters,

298
00:30:56.970 --> 00:31:00.670
living rough, outdoing theIndians at their own game -

299
00:31:00.670 --> 00:31:09.970
so that it was said nofour-legged thing is safe from aFrenchman.

300
00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:12.100
These French Canadians arehunting the biggest

301
00:31:12.100 --> 00:31:20.500
and most elusive of all NorthAmerican deer the moose.

302
00:31:20.500 --> 00:31:24.300
The man in the lead,incidentally, once had to kill abear that was stealing his food.

303
00:31:24.300 --> 00:31:27.970
He had no gun and stabbed itwith a knife on the end of astick.

304
00:32:20.530 --> 00:32:25.600
So rapacious were the huntersthat they had to track fartherand farther into the interior

305
00:32:25.600 --> 00:32:30.730
in order to find enough animalsto kill.

306
00:32:30.730 --> 00:32:33.000
Forsaking the familiar boats ofEurope

307
00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:36.200
they adopted from theIndians the canoe which wasideal,

308
00:32:36.200 --> 00:32:38.100
not only for plying the widerivers

